{
  "texts": [
    "Their framework uses TL on models such as ResNet v1-152, VGG16, Inception-ResNet-v2, and InceptionV4 to produce noteworthy results.",
    "The model evaluation is skewed, however; the models were tested on images with different augmentations, and so the overall accuracies presented are not on uniform training or testing datasets.",
    "Lastly, Liu et al. (2024) present a novel approach to studying morphological disparity and extinction selectivity during the Permian-Triassic Mass Extinction (PTME) through the development of the DeepMorph DL pipeline.",
    "The automated extraction of morphological features from fossil images enable a robust, scalable analysis of biodiversity loss across six marine clades.",
    "The results reveal heterogeneous extinction selectivity, with ammonoids suffering significant disparity loss, while conodonts expanded their morphospace."
  ]
}